edu.stanford.slac.aida.lib.model

Class AidaField

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.slac.aida.lib.model.AidaField

  • public class AidaField
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates an AidaField.

    It is used to represent a single field in AidaChannelConfig.fields that defines the configuration of the ordinal TABLE column to which it is related by ordinal position in the list.

    Note that it uses the Data annotation to provide all the getters and setters. a constructor with all required arguments, and an equals(), hashcode() and toString() method.

    It also uses the NoArgsConstructor annotation to provide a constructor with no arguments.
